==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Alternative spellings===
* '''[[hi-jack]]'''
* '''[[highjack]]'''

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[illegally]] [[stop]] and [[seize]] [[control]] of some [[vehicle]] in order to [[rob]] it or to reach a [[destination]].
# {{computing}} To seize control of a [[network]]ed computer by means of [[infect]]ing it with a [[worm]] or other [[malware]], thereby turning it into a [[zombie]]. 
# {{computing}} To change [[software]] settings without a user's knowledge so as to force that user to visit a certain [[web site]] (''to '''hijack''' a [[browser]]'').

====Translations====
'''seize control of a vehicle'''

*Finnish: [[kaapata]]
*German: [[hijacken]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An instance of hijacking; the [[illegal]] [[seizure]] of a [[vehicle]].

